00:22:58,730 --> 00:22:59,730
What are you looking at?

258
00:22:59,810 --> 00:23:02,150
What can you do about it anyway?

259
00:23:02,230 --> 00:23:03,480
Hand it over.

260
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:06,740
Give it to me.

261
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,860
Your dead meat.

262
00:23:10,490 --> 00:23:11,870
Everybody look up!

263
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:18,040
What you just did has been
caught on camera, so what now?

264
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:19,420
Would you like to hit us again?

265
00:23:20,330 --> 00:23:21,330
We won't hit you back.

266
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:24,670
You guys are all screwed now.

267
00:23:27,970 --> 00:23:29,970
Yes, the police can't hit civilians.

268
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,890
But know this.

269
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,060
You...

270
00:23:35,430 --> 00:23:37,600
Assaulting a police officer

271
00:23:39,390 --> 00:23:41,650
-can also put you behind bars.
-Why you...

272
00:23:41,730 --> 00:23:44,980
Officers in the area will swarm this place
once I press this.

273
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:47,990
Don't belittle us.

274
00:23:48,070 --> 00:23:49,650
I can beat the crap out of you any day.

275
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:51,740
I'm only holding back

276
00:23:52,530 --> 00:23:54,870
because I'm a police officer.

277
00:23:55,950 --> 00:23:58,330
-Do you get that?
-Just so you know,

278
00:23:58,410 --> 00:24:00,460
I'm reporting you for assault.

279
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,330
I'll see you at the station.

280
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:12,760
Shit! Why did you have mess with cops?

281
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:15,220
-This is all because of you.
-Damn it.

282
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,680
If I could,

283
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,980
I'd gladly throw a punch.

284
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:22,440
If I wasn't a police,
I would've beaten him to death.

285
00:24:27,730 --> 00:24:29,400
As you all know,

286
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:31,990
I'm retiring this Friday.

287
00:24:33,870 --> 00:24:34,870
Although

288
00:24:35,580 --> 00:24:36,870
I'm the oldest here,

289
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:39,330
I haven't done anything for you.

290
00:24:40,460 --> 00:24:41,540
I'll pay 100,000 won

291
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:44,080
for each of you at the firing range today,

292
00:24:45,170 --> 00:24:46,000
so fire away.

293
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:48,550
Thank you.

294
00:24:49,550 --> 00:24:50,590
Thank you.

295
00:24:50,670 --> 00:24:53,090
-Thank you.
-It's up to you

296
00:24:53,180 --> 00:24:54,760
to protect yourselves.

297
00:24:55,890 --> 00:24:58,600
Gun related cases like today can happen

298
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:00,390
anytime in Korea now.

299
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:03,350
Illegal homemade firearms, air guns,

300
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:05,440
and even smuggled guns are a possibility.

301
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:07,690
Crimes are getting more vicious.

302
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:10,030
No matter how tired you are
from your workload,

303
00:25:10,610 --> 00:25:11,860
no matter

304
00:25:12,030 --> 00:25:13,910
how expensive it is to practice here,

305
00:25:14,530 --> 00:25:15,820
you should

306
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:19,080
come to the firing range
and practice once a week.

307
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:21,910
-That's how--
-Incidents like today...

308
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,460
Can't be avoided

309
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:26,250
despite our good aim.

310
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,590
He got shot in the head.

311
00:25:31,170 --> 00:25:33,420
Still, you and
Lieutenant Oh hit the suspect

312
00:25:33,510 --> 00:25:34,760
in the arm and leg.

313
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:36,890
It prevented further casualties.

314
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,890
There's a reason why we say

315
00:25:41,890 --> 00:25:44,440
we're in the line of fire.

316
00:25:45,730 --> 00:25:46,900
But what can we do?

317
00:25:47,730 --> 00:25:48,770
That's our job.

318
00:25:49,110 --> 00:25:50,730
We have to go to the scene of crimes.

319
00:25:51,820 --> 00:25:53,070
I'm not smart enough

320
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:56,820
to say something cool to you all.

321
00:25:58,910 --> 00:26:01,790
Just make sure you always stay safe

322
00:26:02,450 --> 00:26:04,750
and retire of old age like me.

323
00:26:05,410 --> 00:26:06,250
Understand?

324
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,420
-Yes.
-Yes.

325
00:26:12,210 --> 00:26:13,760
Some slots have opened up.

326
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,550
Go in and practice.

327
00:26:15,930 --> 00:26:16,930
-Yes.
-Yes.

328
00:26:23,100 --> 00:26:24,520
Why aren't you going in?

329
00:26:28,770 --> 00:26:30,610
You were amazing today.

330
00:26:32,610 --> 00:26:33,940
"I have a partner.

331
00:26:34,490 --> 00:26:35,780
I'm not alone."

332
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:38,950
knowing that, I felt reassured.

333
00:27:15,820 --> 00:27:18,570
Hye-ri, your arms move around too much.

334
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:21,120
-Do more push-ups.
-Yes, sir.

335
00:27:25,950 --> 00:27:28,830
Sang-su, drop your shoulders.

336
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:30,250
Yes, sir.

337
00:27:33,790 --> 00:27:35,960
Jeong-o, you have great form.

338
00:27:49,730 --> 00:27:51,810
Arrest him for blackmailing and calumny.

339
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:54,610
Don't agree to a settlement

340
00:27:54,690 --> 00:27:55,980
even if he begs.

341
00:27:56,690 --> 00:27:57,780
With this as evidence,

342
00:27:57,860 --> 00:28:00,740
his head injury will be ruled
as self-inflicted, so...

343
00:28:05,990 --> 00:28:06,910
Thank you.

344
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:08,910
Thank you so much.

345
00:28:14,210 --> 00:28:15,090
<i>Moving on.</i>

346
00:28:15,170 --> 00:28:17,710
<i>In a Seoul downtown area,
a shocking turn of events occurred</i>

347
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:19,720
<i>when a police officer</i>

348
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,880
<i>was gunned down by a suspect
with a homemade firearm.</i>

349
00:28:22,470 --> 00:28:24,800
<i>Around three o'clock this afternoon</i>

350
00:28:24,890 --> 00:28:26,720
<i>at a three-way intersection
in Mahyeong-gu,</i>

351
00:28:26,810 --> 00:28:29,560
<i>Captain Kang Tae-hun
of Myeongu Patrol Divison</i>

352
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:33,060
<i>responded to an assault case in the area.</i>

353
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:36,900
<i>The suspect in the case fired
his homemade pistol at him.</i>

354
00:28:37,190 --> 00:28:39,820
<i>Captain Kang was shot in the head,</i>

355
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:42,860
<i>and he lost his life at the scene.</i>

356
00:28:42,950 --> 00:28:46,490
<i>The late Captain Kang
fulfilled his duties as an officer</i>

357
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:48,540
<i>despite suffering from gastric cancer.</i>

358
00:28:48,620 --> 00:28:52,040
<i>He was known to always
arrive first at a dangerous scene,</i>

359
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:54,750
<i>which is why this loss is devastating.</i>

360
00:28:54,830 --> 00:28:58,750
<i>The police has announced
a special promotion for Captain Kang...</i>

361
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:02,050
<i>We shared the sad news
of losing Captain Kang Tae-hun,</i>

362
00:29:02,130 --> 00:29:05,260
<i>but not all police officers
have a sense of duty like him.</i>

363
00:29:05,340 --> 00:29:08,140
<i>Despite illegal gambling
and sex trafficking charges,</i>

364
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:10,930
<i>the police officer in question
has not been charged</i>

365
00:29:11,020 --> 00:29:13,560
<i>with an adequate sentence.
Seoul Jangdong Police...</i>

366
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:14,940
Every news outlet

367
00:29:15,020 --> 00:29:17,900
should be reporting
Captain Kang's fall in the line of duty.

368
00:29:18,610 --> 00:29:20,940
Instead they're reporting
on that piece of shit.

369
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:24,780
He must have connections
in the prosecutor's office.

370
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:29,700
Even a 10-year prison sentence
isn't enough for what he did,

371
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:31,870
but how could he get off with a fine?

372
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:36,960
He loses his badge if he gets probation,

373
00:29:37,420 --> 00:29:39,090
so they fined him instead.

374
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:40,800
That's just dirty.

375
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:42,880
I don't know about him but...

376
00:29:42,970 --> 00:29:45,890
I bet he'll get a cushy position soon.
Son of a bitch.

377
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:51,850
Shut your mouths

378
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:53,310
and raise your glasses.

379
00:29:56,020 --> 00:29:57,060
Safety first.

380
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,860
-Safety first.
-Safety first.

381
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:16,960
See you tomorrow.
Another drink and I might cause trouble.

382
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:23,380
-See you tomorrow.
-Take care.

383
00:30:28,180 --> 00:30:29,390
He brought his car.

384
00:30:30,810 --> 00:30:32,970
Don't worry. He called someone.

385
00:30:35,230 --> 00:30:37,690
Let's finish our beers and go home.

386
00:30:37,770 --> 00:30:38,980
Safety first.

387
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:40,310
-Safety first.
-Safety first.

388
00:30:59,460 --> 00:31:01,090
Who were you calling?

389
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,220
Chauffeur service.

390
00:31:10,850 --> 00:31:12,140
I saw the news.

391
00:31:13,510 --> 00:31:15,430
You did well, my husband.

392
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:17,140
Honey.

393
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,270
I don't want to say anything.

394
00:31:23,570 --> 00:31:24,820
Okay.

395
00:31:26,070 --> 00:31:28,650
Get in. I'll take you home.

396
00:31:47,420 --> 00:31:48,300
Aren't you getting in?

397
00:32:51,150 --> 00:32:52,910
HAN-SOL

398
00:33:00,870 --> 00:33:01,960
Hi, Boss.

399
00:33:02,460 --> 00:33:05,670
You retire in two days.
I'm not your boss anymore.

400
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:07,920
Just call me Han-sol.

401
00:33:09,260 --> 00:33:10,300
Should I do that?

402
00:33:12,130 --> 00:33:13,180
Should I

403
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:15,390
call you Han-sol now?

404
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:17,600
Yes.

405
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:23,190
Sam-bo. You did great today,
catching the perpetrator.

406
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,850
Well done.

407
00:33:25,690 --> 00:33:28,980
<i>You did even better by not getting hurt.</i>

408
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:31,240
<i>I commend you for that.</i>

409
00:33:32,530 --> 00:33:33,530
Thank you

410
00:33:35,030 --> 00:33:36,160
for not getting hurt.

411
00:33:36,410 --> 00:33:38,160
<i>The kids got scared.</i>

412
00:33:40,620 --> 00:33:41,620
Boss.

413
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,080
Will you

414
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:47,330
come to my retirement?

415
00:33:47,540 --> 00:33:48,880
<i>Of course.</i>

416
00:33:51,170 --> 00:33:54,130
I can't drink alcohol or be on duty,

417
00:33:56,340 --> 00:33:57,970
but I'll definitely be there.

418
00:34:00,350 --> 00:34:01,430
Thanks.

419
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:04,140
Don't thank me, Lieutenant Lee.

420
00:34:04,690 --> 00:34:07,190
<i>I mean, Sam-bo.</i>

421
00:34:09,980 --> 00:34:12,650
I'll see you then.

422
00:34:15,240 --> 00:34:16,320
Goodbye.

423
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:57,200
A cop can't run away when someone shoots.
He must catch the shooter.

424
00:34:58,450 --> 00:35:00,030
What if he dies?

425
00:35:01,370 --> 00:35:02,580
He didn't die.

426
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:05,250
He didn't die or get hurt today,

427
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:07,080
but what about next time?

428
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:11,210
Cops are human beings too.
Bullets kill them.

429
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:14,250
That goes for Yang-chon and you too.

430
00:35:15,630 --> 00:35:17,760
It's all over once you die.

431
00:35:19,430 --> 00:35:23,390
The pension for dying on the job,
the honor,

432
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:27,730
the respect of others
means nothing once you're dead.

433
00:35:33,610 --> 00:35:35,400
That's a huge kite.

434
00:35:35,650 --> 00:35:36,900
Is it for me?

435
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:39,070
It's for the cop who died today.

436
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:41,410
I want to fly it for him.

437
00:36:16,820 --> 00:36:19,360
What are you thinking about?

438
00:36:21,530 --> 00:36:23,490
About when Captain Kang got shot.

439
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:29,460
I felt sorry for his partner
who was dazed and shocked.

440
00:36:32,830 --> 00:36:34,840
What's the difference

441
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:38,710
between him and me right now?

442
00:36:43,640 --> 00:36:45,300
What's the worst part?

443
00:36:50,390 --> 00:36:51,980
The fact that someone died.

444
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:56,400
"I'm so glad I didn't die.

445
00:36:58,730 --> 00:37:00,820
I'm glad it wasn't someone
from my division.

446
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,410
I'm so glad."

447
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:12,460
I keep having such selfish thoughts.

448
00:37:39,270 --> 00:37:40,730
GOVERNMENT FUNDED
STUDY ABROAD PROGRAM

449
00:37:40,820 --> 00:37:44,860
<i>During the day I heard about
the shooting in your district,</i>

450
00:37:45,070 --> 00:37:47,490
<i>and tonight they did a report
on random killings on the news.</i>

451
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:49,830
All that is keeping me up.

452
00:37:50,870 --> 00:37:54,750
<i>Jeong-o, is it okay to be a cop?</i>

453
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,880
Others do it, so why can't I?

454
00:37:57,380 --> 00:38:01,130
<i>When can you apply to go abroad
on that thing you mentioned?</i>

455
00:38:01,210 --> 00:38:03,170
I don't qualify yet.

456
00:38:09,850 --> 00:38:12,390
There's a good opportunity.

457
00:38:12,810 --> 00:38:14,690
I want to apply
for a government funded program.

458
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:21,400
That'll work as an advantage when I apply
for a promotion or to work abroad.

459
00:38:22,030 --> 00:38:24,490
<i>I'm glad you're considering that.</i>

460
00:38:24,570 --> 00:38:26,700
<i>Then you can quit
working at your division soon.</i>

461
00:38:26,780 --> 00:38:28,910
<i>And you won't have to go back there.</i>

462
00:38:29,490 --> 00:38:32,410
<i>I'm so scared about you working there.</i>

463
00:38:32,580 --> 00:38:34,660
<i>My heart pounds so fast.</i>

464
00:38:34,750 --> 00:38:38,080
<i>The panic disorder I'm finally
recovering from might come back.</i>

465
00:38:38,580 --> 00:38:41,500
Okay. I get it, so hang up.

466
00:38:42,710 --> 00:38:44,800
Jeong-o, come and sleep with me.

467
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:47,130
I keep waking up.

468
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:50,180
Mom, I have to go. Sleep well.

469
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:54,560
Go to bed. I'll join you soon.

470
00:39:29,180 --> 00:39:30,140
I like you.

471
00:39:32,140 --> 00:39:33,100
I like you too.

472
00:39:56,580 --> 00:39:57,660
Jeong-o.

473
00:39:59,410 --> 00:40:02,790
Are you really going to study abroad
on the government scholarship

474
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,710
and work somewhere overseas after that?

475
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,800
What about Sang-su?

476
00:40:13,220 --> 00:40:15,930
It looks like he'll stay at the division.

477
00:40:17,350 --> 00:40:18,640
Will you break up with him?

478
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:24,150
Just go to sleep.

479
00:40:51,260 --> 00:40:52,510
Her tongue has been cut off.

480
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:29,000
The random attacks where civilians
are getting stabbed

481
00:41:29,500 --> 00:41:32,090
and sprayed with flour have been
spreading from Jangnam to Jangdong.

482
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:33,880
Our precinct isn't safe.

483
00:41:35,010 --> 00:41:37,680
Hence, I've decided to carry a gun
with me at all times from now on.

484
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:42,480
From Captain Kang's case,
I learned that taser guns can't shoot far

485
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:45,480
and the effects only last a few seconds,
so it's hard to detain suspects.

486
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:49,690
I heard Sergeant Kang was the only one
who hit the suspect with the taser.

487
00:41:49,780 --> 00:41:51,690
Just carry a taser gun.

488
00:41:52,570 --> 00:41:54,780
Sergeant Kang was supposed
to have a gun on him.

489
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:58,780
It hurts our back, but there's a reason
why we carry taser guns.

490
00:41:58,910 --> 00:42:00,830
In this country,

491
00:42:01,580 --> 00:42:04,040
guns aren't used to shoot perps.
Haven't you heard that we cops

492
00:42:04,120 --> 00:42:05,920
are better off throwing them at perps?

493
00:42:07,580 --> 00:42:09,590
The suspect yesterday wasn't moving,

494
00:42:09,670 --> 00:42:13,510
so Lieutenant Oh and Lieutenant Lee
could shoot him in the arm and leg.

495
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:15,130
But most of the time, they move.

496
00:42:16,130 --> 00:42:18,140
What if you end up killing the suspect?

497
00:42:19,510 --> 00:42:21,060
I don't even want to think about it.

498
00:42:21,140 --> 00:42:23,430
Plus, you'll be investigated
by Internal Affairs right away

499
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:24,810
and go to trial too.

500
00:42:24,940 --> 00:42:27,600
That's right.
Last year, an officer shot a robber,

501
00:42:27,690 --> 00:42:29,230
who ended up with a full-body paralysis,

502
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:31,610
and the officer got fired
for excessive use of force.

503
00:42:32,190 --> 00:42:33,150
He got fired?

504
00:42:34,690 --> 00:42:37,450
I'm sure he shot the guy
because he had no other choice.

505
00:42:37,530 --> 00:42:39,320
Everyone,
from the government to the citizens,

506
00:42:39,700 --> 00:42:42,080
wants us to catch criminals
with our bare hands.

507
00:42:42,740 --> 00:42:44,580
A few years back in Cheongma,

508
00:42:44,660 --> 00:42:47,960
an officer was killed by bastards
causing a scene with axes.

509
00:42:48,830 --> 00:42:51,670
Because using a gun almost always
leads to disciplinary action,

510
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,920
he tried to stop them
without shooting them.

511
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:56,800
But as for Captain Kang's case,

512
00:42:57,470 --> 00:42:59,760
the perp used a gun, and a cop died.

513
00:43:00,930 --> 00:43:03,600
The media and the prosecution
can't criticize us for shooting him,

514
00:43:04,020 --> 00:43:06,180
-but in most cases--
-Perps use knives.

515
00:43:07,850 --> 00:43:09,310
Sometimes, they use axes or pickaxes.

